$ ~/.local

? `~/.local` is commonly used for installing software locally, notably by `→ development/languages/Python/installation/directory/Scripts/pip` in conjuction with the `--user` command line option.

sa:
 `→ Linux/fhs/home/username/_local/bin[~/local/bin]` is recommended by the → https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/basedir-spec-latest.html[XDG standard] to store executables.
